info.description: Say bye bye to Lorem ipsum! Used to generate random data for all kinds of purposes. Generated data is mimicking something that might be in the real world.

aircraftType.description: Returns a random aircraft type: regional, narrowbody or widebody.

airlineName.description: Returns a random airline name. For example: Sky Airline.

airlineCode.description: Returns a random airline IATA code. For example: H2.

airplaneName.description: Returns a random airplane name. For example: De Havilland DH.104 Dove.

airplaneTypeCode.description: Returns a random airplane name. For example: DHD.

departureAirportName.description: Returns a random departure airport name. For example: Indira Gandhi International Airport.

departureAirportCode.description: Returns a random departure airport IATA code. For example: DEL.

arrivalAirportName.description: Returns a random arrival airport name. For example: Perth Airport.

arrivalAirportCode.description: Returns a random arrival airport IATA code. For example: PER.

flightNumber.description: Returns a random flight number. For example: H20316. Flight numbers are 1 to 4 numbers long. Leading zeros are added as well as airline IATA code to generate commonly used format.

recordLocator.description: Returns a random record locator. For example: ACWNMD. Airlines commonly use this to identify reservations. Can be used as a booking reference, confirmation codes etc.

seat.description: Returns a random seat. For example: 14A. Property uses generated Aircraft Type as input for consistensy.

get.description: Generate aviation related data. You can use this endpoint for creating realistic mock data for flights or tickets. Returns an array of airline related properties, by default ten.

bear.description: Returns a random breed of bear. For example: Polar bear.

bird.description: Returns a random breed of bird. For example: Eurasian Wigeon.

cat.description: Returns a random breed of cat. For example: Birman.

cetacean.description: Returns a random breed of cetacean. For example: Short-Beaked Common Dolphin.

cow.description: Returns a random breed of cow. For example: Deep Red cattle.

crocodilia.description: Returns a random breed of crocodilia. For example: Philippine Crocodile.

dog.description: Returns a random breed of dog. For example: Molossus of Epirus.

fish.description: Returns a random breed of fish. For example: Indian mackerel.

horse.description: Returns a random breed of horse. For example: Fleuve.

insect.description: Returns a random breed of insect. For example: German yellowjacket.

lion.description: Returns a random breed of lion. For example: Asiatic Lion.

rabbit.description: Returns a random breed of rabbit. For example: Flemish Giant.

rodent.description: Returns a random breed of rodent. For example: Rodent.

snake.description: Returns a random breed of snake. For example: Barred wolf snake.

type.description: Returns a random type of animal. For example: dog.

get.description: Generate different kinds of animal species. Returns an array of animal species, by default ten. All values may be localized.

cmyk.description: Returns a random CMYK color decimal values.

colorByCSSColorSpace.description: Returns a random CSS color decimal values.

cssSupportedFunction.description: Returns a random CSS supported color function name. Options are: cmyk, color, hsl, hsla, hwb, lab, lch, rgb or rgba. For example: lch.

cssSupportedSpace.description: Returns a random CSS supported color space name. Options are: a98-rgb, display-p3, prophoto-rgb, rec2020, sRGB. For example: rec2020.

hsl.description: Returns a random hsl color decimal values.

human.description: Returns a random human readable color name. For example turquoise.

hwb.description: Returns a random hwb color decimal values.

lab.description: Returns a random lab color decimal values.

lch.description: Returns a random lch color decimal values.

rgb.description: Returns a random RGB color in hex format. For example: #be7fcc.

space.description: Returns a random color space name. For example: CIEUVW.

get.description: Generate color related data. Includes color values in different formats as well as human readable value. Returns an array of colors, by default ten. Some values may be localized.

buzzAdjective.description: Returns a random buzz adjective. For example: extensible.

buzzNoun.description: Returns a random buzz noun. For example: initiatives.

buzzPhrase.description: Returns a random buzz phrase. For example: mesh clicks-and-mortar eyeballs.

buzzVerb.description: Returns a random buzz verb. For example: expedite.

catchPhrase.description: Returns a random catch phrase. For example: Business-focused responsive moratorium.

catchPhraseAdjective.description: Returns a random catch phrase adjective. For example: Integrated.

catchPhraseDescriptor.description: Returns a random catch phrase descriptor. For example: uniform.

catchPhraseNoun.description: Returns a random catch phrase noun. For example: focus group.

city.description: Returns a random city. For example: Weissnatchester.

country.description: Returns a random country. For example: Saudi Arabia.

creditLimit.description: Returns a random credit limit. This is a integer from 1 to 100 million. Displayed in millions. For example: 9000000.

email.description: Returns a random email. For example: Dylan4@gmail.com.

mobilePhone.description: Returns a random mobile phone number. For example: (337) 925-6199.

name.description: Returns a random name. For example: Dibbert, Kirlin and Hammes.

numberOfEmployees.description: Returns a random number of employees. This is a number between 1 and 10 000. For example: 9820.

phone.description: Returns a random phone number. For example: (836) 964-9811.

revenue.description: Returns a random revenue. This is a integer between 1 and 100 million. Displayed in millions. For example: 8000000.

streetAddress.description: Returns a random street address. For example: 78999 Zemlak Field.

website.description: Returns a random website. For example: https://visible-derivative.com/.

zipCode.description: Returns a random zip code. For example: 54306-5071.

get.description: Generate company related data, like names and company jargon. Returns an array of properties, by default ten. Some of the properties can be localized.
Generate database related technical data, like columns or engines. Returns an array of properties, by default ten.

anytime.description: Returns a random date and time. Can be in the future or in the past. For example: 2023-12-30T01:54:24.658Z.

birthdate.description: Returns a random birthdate for an adult. For example: 1948-06-14T08:47:26.296Z.

future.description: Returns a random future date and time. For example: 2024-06-01T09:36:53.510Z.

month.description: Returns a random month name. For example: March.

past.description: Returns a random past date and time. For example: 2023-08-20T17:40:37.262Z.

recent.description: Returns a random recent date and time in recent past, at most 5 days away. For example: 2024-01-02T03:09:38.383Z.

soon.description: Returns a random date and time in the near future, at most 5 days away. For example: 2024-01-03T11:00:08.493Z.

weekday.description: Returns a random weekday name. For example: Friday.

year.description: Returns a random year between 1900 and 2100. For example: 2083.

get.description: Generate datetime data. While seed usage is available, note that most of the properties depend on the time the enpoint is requested, rather than a spesific seed value. Returns an array of properties, by default ten. All dates are returned as ISO-8601 datetime strings. Month and weekday might be localized.

accountName.description: Returns a random account name. For example: Savings Account.

accountNumber.description: Returns a random account number in local format. For example: 54296344.

amount.description: Returns a random amount for a transaction. Value has two decimal places. For example: 540.29.

bic.description: Returns a random BIC (Bank Identifier Code). For example: OSCTPNT6A96.

bitcoinAddress.description: Returns a random Bitcoin address. For example: 36ks9VMpLaFeWbR8hu1Uuz4zgbUid4XWvn.

creditCardCVV.description: Returns a random Credit Card CVV. For example: 400.

creditCardIssuer.description: Returns a random Credit Card Issuer. For example: visa.

creditCardNumber.description: Returns a random Credit Card Number from the issuer from the issuer property. For example: 4584186609458.

currencyCode.description: Returns a random Currency Code. Currency Code, Currency Name and Currency Symmbol are from them same currency. For example: TRY.

currencyName.description: Returns a random Currency Name. Currency Code, Currency Name and Currency Symmbol are from them same currency. For example: Turkish Lira.

currencySymbol.description: Returns a random Currency Symbol. Currency Code, Currency Name and Currency Symmbol are from them same currency. For example: â‚º.

ethereumAddress.description: Returns a random Ethereum Address. For example: 0x83a44fb302d6d7a68fcdac2b2efdfc3e0ea53c2a.

iban.description: Returns a random IBAN (International Bank Account Number). For example: GL3144820110800764.

litecoinAddress.description: Returns a random Litecoin Address. For example: Ljo4LU3FMxfVyVF7sTVvDzfBhp.

maskedNumber.description: Returns a random Masked Number. For example: (â€¦0859).

pin.description: Returns a random PIN (Personal Identification Number). For example: 1309.

routingNumber.description: Returns a random Routing Number. For example: 164294325.

transactionDescription.description: Returns a random Transaction Description. For example: deposit transaction at Reinger, Hamill and Gutmann using card ending with ***(...3677) for TJS 820.80 in account ***44178655.

transactionType.description: Returns a random Transaction Type. For example: payment.

get.description: Generate finance related data, like credit card information, account information and so on. Returns an array of properties, by default ten. Some properties might be localized.

branch.description: Returns the branch name of the commit. For example: interface-compress.

commitDate.description: Returns the date and time of the commit. Formatting is the same as in git log. For example: Tue Jan 2 18:12:21 2024 +0300.

commitEntry.description: Returns the full commit entry, including the commit SHA, author, date, and message.

commitMessage.description: Returns the commit message. For example: compress open-source array.

commitSha.description: Returns the SHA of the commit. For example: b5daadecfa08c22c5fea7ba3c0fdc5bdff4bab87.

get.description: Generate git related data. Returns an array of properties, by default ten.

abbreviation.description: Returns an abbreviation from technologies. For example: XSS.

adjective.description: Returns a hacker or technology related adjective. For example: 1080p.

ingverb.description: Returns a verb ending in -ing. For example: quantifying.

noun.description: Returns a hacker or technology related noun. For example: card.

phrase.description: Returns a hacker or technology related phrase. For example: I'll connect the open-source RSS interface, that should circuit the VGA transmitter!.

verb.description: Returns a hacker or technology related verb. For example: override.

get.description: Generate hacker or IT related buzzwords. Returns an array of properties, by default ten. Some properties might be localized.

parameters.name: width
parameters.description: Define the width of the image. Default is 640.

parameters.name: height
parameters.description: Define the height of the image. Default is 480.

parameters.name: category
parameters.description: Define the category of the image. Default is blank and returns an image from a random category.

color.description: Returns a random color code in hex format. For example: #511134.

displayName.description: Returns a display name for a given user. All user related properties use the same first and lastname as a base. For example: Ted.Runolfsson48.

domainName.description: Returns a random domain name. For example: clear-operating.info.

domainSuffix.description: Returns a domain suffix. For example: net.

domainWord.description: Returns a random word to be used in a domain. For example: sparkling-bather.

email.description: Returns an email address. For example: Ted_Runolfsson10@yahoo.com.

emoji.description: Returns a random emoji. For example: ðŸ˜º.

exampleEmail.description: Returns an example email address. All user related properties use the same first and lastname as a base. For example: Ted_Runolfsson88@example.net.

httpMethod.description: Returns a HTTP method. For example: PUT.

httpStatusCode.description: Returns a HTTP status code. For example: 103.

ip.description: Returns a random IPv4 or IPv6 address. For example: b8bb:21ac:da45:baf2:fe1c:7e62:7f2c:c6dc.

ipv4.description: Returns an IPv4 address. For example: 146.120.42.165.

ipv6.description: Returns an IPv6 address. For example: 1eff:77af:b6d3:ae02:8e0d:1d7d:feb2:7a01.

mac.description: Returns a MAC address. For example: c8:14:d0:db:1e:d4.

password.description: Returns a random string to be used as a password. For example: eqv2uVVHsXkWcRs.

port.description: Returns a random port number. For example: 5071.

protocol.description: Returns a protocol. For example: https.

url.description: Returns a random URL. For example: https://immaculate-debtor.biz.

userAgent.description: Returns a random user agent. For example: Mozilla/5.0 (X11; Linux x86_64 AppleWebKit/532.2.0 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/18.0.884.0 Safari/532.2.0.

userName.description: Returns a user name. All user related properties use the same first and lastname as a base. For example: Ted42.

buildingNumber.description: Returns a building number. For example: 79502.

cardinalDirection.description: Returns a cardinal direction. For example: South.

country.description: Returns a country name. For example: Faroe Islands.

direction.description: Returns a direction. For example: Southeast.
